  "question": "ACID Properties",
  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>ACID Properties Interactive Explorer</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    background: white;\n    color: black;\n    margin: 1em;\n  }\n  hr {\n    margin: 1em 0;\n  }\n  textarea {\n    width: 100%;\n    height: 4em;\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n  }\n  input[type=number] {\n    width: 5em;\n  }\n  button {\n    margin: 0.2em 0.3em 0.2em 0;\n  }\n  label {\n    user-select: none;\n  }\n  .section {\n    margin-bottom: 2em;\n  }\n  .log {\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 0.5em;\n    height: 10em;\n    overflow-y: scroll;\n    font-size: 0.9em;\n  }\n  .state-box {\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 0.5em;\n    min-height: 3em;\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n  }\n  table {\n    border-collapse: collapse;\n    margin-top: 0.5em;\n  }\n  td, th {\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 0.2em 0.5em;\n    text-align: left;\n  }\n  .input-inline {\n    display: inline-block;\n    margin-right: 1em;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>ACID Properties Interactive Explorer</h1>\n<p>This tool lets you interactively explore the ACID (Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, Durability) properties in database transactions. You can create transactions, add operations, simulate failures, and observe effects on data and logs. Controls are minimalistic. Use the sections and interact to deeply explore how ACID works.</p>\n\n<hr />\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"global-db-section\">\n<h2>Global Database State</h2>\n<p>Current database state (key-value pairs):</p>\n<div class=\"state-box\" id=\"db-state-box\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-label=\"Current database state\"></div>\n<button id=\"reset-db-btn\" type=\"button\">Reset Database to Default</button>\n<button id=\"clear-db-btn\" type=\"button\">Clear Database</button>\n</div>\n\n<hr />\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"transaction-builder\">\n<h2>Create & Manage Transactions</h2>\n<div>\n<label for=\"trans-id-input\" class=\"input-inline\">Transaction ID:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"trans-id-input\" placeholder=\"T1\" />\n<button id=\"create-trans-btn\" type=\"button\">Create Transaction</button>\n<button id=\"commit-trans-btn\" type=\"button\" disabled>Commit Transaction</button>\n<button id=\"abort-trans-btn\" type=\"button\" disabled>Abort Transaction</button>\n<button id=\"clear-trans-btn\" type=\"button\" disabled>Clear Transaction Ops</button>\n</div>\n<div id=\"current-trans-info\" style=\"margin-top:0.5em;\"></div>\n\n<div style=\"margin-top:1em;\">\n<h3>Add Operation to Transaction</h3>\n<label for=\"op-type-select\" class=\"input-inline\">Operation:</label>\n<select id=\"op-type-select\" aria-label=\"Select operation type\">\n  <option value=\"read\">READ</option>\n  <option value=\"write\">WRITE</option>\n</select>\n\n<label for=\"op-key-input\" class=\"input-inline\">Key:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"op-key-input\" size=\"8\" placeholder=\"key\" />\n\n<label for=\"op-value-input\" class=\"input-inline\" id=\"value-label\" style=\"display:none;\">Value:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"op-value-input\" size=\"12\" placeholder=\"value\" style=\"display:none;\" />\n\n<button id=\"add-op-btn\" type=\"button\" disabled>Add Operation</button>\n</div>\n\n<div style=\"margin-top:1em;\">\n<h3>Transaction Operations</h3>\n<div class=\"state-box\" id=\"trans-ops-box\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-label=\"Transaction operations list\" style=\"height:6em; overflow-y:auto; font-size:0.95em;\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<hr />\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"execution-section\">\n<h2>Execute Transactions and Simulate</h2>\n<p>\nSelect isolation level, durability persistence, and simulate advanced scenarios:\n</p>\n<div>\n<label for=\"isolation-select\" class=\"input-inline\">Isolation level:</label>\n<select id=\"isolation-select\" aria-label=\"Choose isolation level\">\n  <option value=\"read_uncommitted\">Read Uncommitted</option>\n  <option value=\"read_committed\">Read Committed</option>\n  <option value=\"repeatable_read\">Repeatable Read</option>\n  <option value=\"serializable\" selected>Serializable</option>\n</select>\n\n<label for=\"durability-checkbox\" class=\"input-inline\" style=\"margin-left:1em;\">\n  <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"durability-checkbox\" checked /> Durability (Persist commits)\n</label>\n</div>\n\n<div style=\"margin-top:1em;\">\n<button id=\"start-exec-btn\" type=\"button\" disabled>Start Execution (Run Transaction)</button>\n<button id=\"simulate-failure-btn\" type=\"button\" disabled>Simulate Failure During Execution</button>\n</div>\n\n<div style=\"margin-top:1em;\">\n<h3>Execution Log</h3>\n<div class=\"log\" id=\"exec-log\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-atomic=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<hr />\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"exploration-tools\">\n<h2>Exploration Tools & Controls</h2>\n<p>Use these tools to deeply explore scenarios, simulate crashes, resets, and advanced workflows.</p>\n<div>\n<button id=\"simulate-crash-btn\" type=\"button\" disabled>Simulate System Crash (Hard Reset)</button>\n<button id=\"recover-db-btn\" type=\"button\" disabled>Recover Database From Durability Log</button>\n<button id=\"view-durability-log-btn\" type=\"button\">View Durability Log</button>\n<button id=\"clear-log-btn\" type=\"button\">Clear Execution Log</button>\n</div>\n\n<div style=\"margin-top:1em;\">\n<label><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"auto-step-checkbox\" /> Auto-step execution with 1.5s delay</label>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<hr />\n\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"durability-log-section\" style=\"display:none;\">\n<h2>Durability Log (Committed Transactions)</h2>\n<div class=\"state-box\" id=\"durability-log-box\" style=\"height: 8em; overflow-y:auto;\"></div>\n<button id=\"close-durability-log-btn\" type=\"button\">Close Durability Log</button>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n(() => {\n  \"use strict\";\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Data Structures and Globals\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  // Default initial database state (key-value store)\n  const DEFAULT_DB = {\n    itemA: \"10\",\n    itemB: \"20\",\n    itemC: \"30\"\n  };\n\n  // Global database state (in-memory)\n  let db = {...DEFAULT_DB};\n\n  // Durability log: Array of committed transactions\n  // Each entry: {id: \"T1\", operations: [{op, key, value?}], timestamp, isolation, committedState}\n  let durabilityLog = [];\n\n  // Current transaction in construction\n  let currentTransaction = null;\n\n  // Transaction Execution State:\n  // Executing transaction and its intermediate states\n  let execState = null;\n\n  // Auto-step flag and timer handle\n  let autoStep = false;\n  let autoStepTimer = null;\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Utilities\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  function logExec(msg) {\n    const logEl = document.getElementById(\"exec-log\");\n    logEl.textContent += msg + \"\\n\";\n    logEl.scrollTop = logEl.scrollHeight;\n  }\n\n  function clearExecLog() {\n    document.getElementById(\"exec-log\").textContent = \"\";\n  }\n\n  // Format key-values as simple lines\n  function formatKV(state) {\n    if (!state || Object.keys(state).length === 0) return \"(empty)\";\n    return Object.entries(state)\n      .map(([k,v]) => k + \" = \" + v)\n      .join(\"\\n\");\n  }\n\n  // Display database state\n  function updateDBStateBox() {\n    const box = document.getElementById(\"db-state-box\");\n    box.textContent = formatKV(db);\n  }\n\n  // Display current transaction operations\n  function updateTransOpsBox() {\n    const box = document.getElementById(\"trans-ops-box\");\n    if (!currentTransaction) {\n      box.textContent = \"(No transaction selected)\";\n      return;\n    }\n    if (currentTransaction.operations.length===0) {\n      box.textContent = \"(No operations added)\";\n      return;\n    }\n    const lines = currentTransaction.operations.map((op,i) => {\n      if (op.op===\"read\") return `${i+1}. READ  key='${op.key}'`;\n      if (op.op===\"write\") return `${i+1}. WRITE key='${op.key}' value='${op.value}'`;\n      return `${i+1}. UNKNOWN OP`;\n    });\n    box.textContent = lines.join(\"\\n\");\n  }\n\n  // Display current transaction info\n  function updateCurrentTransactionInfo() {\n    const info = document.getElementById(\"current-trans-info\");\n    if (!currentTransaction) {\n      info.textContent = \"No transaction created.\";\n      return;\n    }\n    info.textContent =\n      `Transaction ID: ${currentTransaction.id}\\n` +\n      `Operations: ${currentTransaction.operations.length}`;\n  }\n\n  // Enable/disable buttons based on states\n  function refreshUI() {\n    // Buttons related to transaction creation & manipulation\n    document.getElementById(\"commit-trans-btn\").disabled = !currentTransaction || currentTransaction.operations.length===0 || execState !== null;\n    document.getElementById(\"abort-trans-btn\").disabled = !currentTransaction || execState !== null;\n    document.getElementById(\"clear-trans-btn\").disabled = !currentTransaction || currentTransaction.operations.length===0 || execState !== null;\n\n    // Add op button enabled only if current transaction exists, key valid, (and value if write)\n    const addOpBtn = document.getElementById(\"add-op-btn\");\n    if (!currentTransaction) {\n      addOpBtn.disabled = true;\n    } else {\n      const keyInput = document.getElementById(\"op-key-input\").value.trim();\n      const opType = document.getElementById(\"op-type-select\").value;\n      if (opType===\"read\") {\n        addOpBtn.disabled = keyInput.length===0;\n      } else {\n        // write op requires value\n        const valInput = document.getElementById(\"op-value-input\").value.trim();\n        addOpBtn.disabled = keyInput.length===0 || valInput.length===0;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Exec buttons enabled only if a transaction exists and not executing now\n    const canExec = currentTransaction && currentTransaction.operations.length>0 && execState === null;\n    document.getElementById(\"start-exec-btn\").disabled = !canExec;\n    document.getElementById(\"simulate-failure-btn\").disabled = execState === null; // only enabled if execution active\n\n    // Exploration buttons enabled only when there's logs or durability logs\n    const hasDurability = durabilityLog.length > 0;\n    const isExecuting = execState !== null;\n\n    document.getElementById(\"simulate-crash-btn\").disabled = !isExecuting;\n    document.getElementById(\"recover-db-btn\").disabled = !hasDurability;\n  }\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Transaction & Operation Data Structures\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  function createTransaction(id) {\n    return {\n      id: id,\n      operations: [],\n      state: \"created\" // created, committed, aborted, executing, finished\n    };\n  }\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Elements for event binding\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  const transIdInput = document.getElementById(\"trans-id-input\");\n  const createTransBtn = document.getElementById(\"create-trans-btn\");\n  const commitTransBtn = document.getElementById(\"commit-trans-btn\");\n  const abortTransBtn = document.getElementById(\"abort-trans-btn\");\n  const clearTransBtn = document.getElementById(\"clear-trans-btn\");\n\n  const opTypeSelect = document.getElementById(\"op-type-select\");\n  const opKeyInput = document.getElementById(\"op-key-input\");\n  const opValueInput = document.getElementById(\"op-value-input\");\n  const valueLabel = document.getElementById(\"value-label\");\n  const addOpBtn = document.getElementById(\"add-op-btn\");\n\n  const startExecBtn = document.getElementById(\"start-exec-btn\");\n  const simulateFailureBtn = document.getElementById(\"simulate-failure-btn\");\n  const isolationSelect = document.getElementById(\"isolation-select\");\n  const durabilityCheckbox = document.getElementById(\"durability-checkbox\");\n\n  const simulateCrashBtn = document.getElementById(\"simulate-crash-btn\");\n  const recoverDbBtn = document.getElementById(\"recover-db-btn\");\n  const viewDurabilityLogBtn = document.getElementById(\"view-durability-log-btn\");\n  const durabilityLogSection = document.getElementById(\"durability-log-section\");\n  const durabilityLogBox = document.getElementById(\"durability-log-box\");\n  const closeDurabilityLogBtn = document.getElementById(\"close-durability-log-btn\");\n\n  const resetDbBtn = document.getElementById(\"reset-db-btn\");\n  const clearDbBtn = document.getElementById(\"clear-db-btn\");\n\n  const clearLogBtn = document.getElementById(\"clear-log-btn\");\n  const autoStepCheckbox = document.getElementById(\"auto-step-checkbox\");\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Event listeners for transaction creation and operation inputs\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  createTransBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    const id = transIdInput.value.trim();\n    if (!id) {\n      alert(\"Please enter a Transaction ID.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    currentTransaction = createTransaction(id);\n    updateCurrentTransactionInfo();\n    updateTransOpsBox();\n    refreshUI();\n    clearExecLog();\n    logExec(`Transaction '${id}' created.`);\n  });\n\n  // Enable/disable Add Operation button dynamically\n  function updateAddOpBtnState() {\n    if (!currentTransaction) {\n      addOpBtn.disabled = true;\n      return;\n    }\n    const keyVal = opKeyInput.value.trim();\n    const opType = opTypeSelect.value;\n    if (opType===\"read\") {\n      addOpBtn.disabled = keyVal.length===0;\n    } else {\n      const valueVal = opValueInput.value.trim();\n      addOpBtn.disabled = keyVal.length===0 || valueVal.length===0;\n    }\n  }\n\n  opKeyInput.addEventListener(\"input\", updateAddOpBtnState);\n  opValueInput.addEventListener(\"input\", updateAddOpBtnState);\n\n  // Show/hide value input on opType change\n  opTypeSelect.addEventListener(\"change\", () => {\n    if (opTypeSelect.value === \"write\") {\n      opValueInput.style.display = \"inline\";\n      valueLabel.style.display = \"inline\";\n    } else {\n      opValueInput.style.display = \"none\";\n      valueLabel.style.display = \"none\";\n      opValueInput.value = \"\";\n    }\n    updateAddOpBtnState();\n  });\n\n  addOpBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (!currentTransaction) return;\n    let opType = opTypeSelect.value;\n    let key = opKeyInput.value.trim();\n    if (!key) return;\n\n    if (opType === \"read\") {\n      currentTransaction.operations.push({op: \"read\", key});\n      logExec(`Operation added: READ key='${key}'`);\n    } else {\n      let value = opValueInput.value.trim();\n      if (!value) return;\n      currentTransaction.operations.push({op: \"write\", key, value});\n      logExec(`Operation added: WRITE key='${key}', value='${value}'`);\n    }\n    updateTransOpsBox();\n    updateCurrentTransactionInfo();\n    refreshUI();\n    // clear inputs\n    opKeyInput.value = \"\";\n    opValueInput.value = \"\";\n    updateAddOpBtnState();\n  });\n\n  // Clear transaction operations\n  clearTransBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (!currentTransaction) return;\n    currentTransaction.operations = [];\n    updateTransOpsBox();\n    updateCurrentTransactionInfo();\n    refreshUI();\n    logExec(`Transaction '${currentTransaction.id}' operations cleared.`);\n  });\n\n  // Abort transaction\n  abortTransBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (!currentTransaction) return;\n    currentTransaction.state = \"aborted\";\n    logExec(`Transaction '${currentTransaction.id}' aborted.`);\n    currentTransaction = null;\n    updateTransOpsBox();\n    updateCurrentTransactionInfo();\n    refreshUI();\n  });\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Database management buttons\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  resetDbBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    db = {...DEFAULT_DB};\n    updateDBStateBox();\n    logExec(\"Database reset to default state.\");\n  });\n\n  clearDbBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    db = {};\n    updateDBStateBox();\n    logExec(\"Database cleared (empty state).\");\n  });\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Execution logic\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  /*\n   Execution model with support for isolation levels:\n   - We will simulate a single transaction execution each time with selected isolation level:\n     - read_uncommitted: reads see uncommitted writes of self only\n     - read_committed: reads see committed database state (simulate snapshot before starting txn)\n     - repeatable_read: reads see stable snapshot of committed DB at transaction start (cache reads)\n     - serializable: same as repeatable_read but with strict ordering checks (no write conflicts allowed)\n\n   For simplicity, simulate only single transaction execution at a time, but the logged durability log\n   contains a history of committed transactions, which can be recovered (durability).\n\n   Atomicity will be illustrated by ability to abort mid-execution (rolling back all writes).\n\n   Consistency implies operations produce valid db states (no invalid keys/values: we keep strings).\n\n   Durability is simulated with persistence in durabilityLog and recovery.\n\n   Isolation effects are simplified with snapshot rules and visibility of writes.\n\n  */\n\n  // Helper: shallow copy db\n  function cloneDB(src) {\n    return {...src};\n  }\n\n  // Execution state machine for current transaction\n  // properties: txn, isolation, durabilityEnabled, stepIndex, workingDB, readCache, writes, aborted\n  // workingDB is current DB snapshot visible to the transaction\n  // readCache caches read values for repeatable reads isolation\n\n  function startExecution(txn, isolationLevel, durabilityEnabled) {\n    if (execState !== null) {\n      logExec(\"Execution already in progress.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    // Validate transaction state\n    if (!txn || txn.operations.length === 0) {\n      logExec(\"No transaction or operations to execute.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    logExec(`Starting execution of Transaction '${txn.id}' with isolation '${isolationLevel}' and durability ${durabilityEnabled?\"ENABLED\":\"DISABLED\"}...`);\n\n    // Prepare working db snapshot according to isolation\n    let workingDB;\n    switch (isolationLevel) {\n      case \"read_uncommitted\":\n        // Always see latest DB (including own writes)\n        workingDB = db;\n        break;\n      case \"read_committed\":\n        // Snapshot committed DB at start (clone)\n        workingDB = cloneDB(db);\n        break;\n      case \"repeatable_read\":\n      case \"serializable\":\n        // Stable snapshot at start (clone DB)\n        workingDB = cloneDB(db);\n        break;\n      default:\n        workingDB = cloneDB(db);\n    }\n\n    execState = {\n      txn: txn,\n      isolation: isolationLevel,\n      durability: durabilityEnabled,\n      stepIndex: 0,\n      workingDB: workingDB,\n      aborted: false,\n      committedWrites: {},   // track writes to commit on success\n      readCache: {},         // for repeatable read caching reads\n      finished: false,\n      simulateFailure: false,\n      serializableWrites: new Set(), // keys written for serializable check\n    };\n\n    // Disable UI buttons that would conflict\n    refreshUI();\n\n    // Begin stepping automatically if selected\n    if (autoStep) {\n      scheduleAutoStep();\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Step through the execution of the transaction:\n  // returns true if still running, false if finished (committed or aborted)\n  function stepExecution() {\n    if (execState === null) {\n      logExec(\"No execution in progress.\");\n      refreshUI();\n      return false;\n    }\n    if (execState.aborted) {\n      logExec(\"Transaction aborted during execution.\");\n      execState.finished = true;\n      execState = null;\n      refreshUI();\n      return false;\n    }\n    if (execState.finished) {\n      logExec(\"Execution already finished.\");\n      execState = null;\n      refreshUI();\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    let st = execState;\n\n    if (st.stepIndex >= st.txn.operations.length) {\n      // All operations done, commit\n      return commitExecution();\n    }\n\n    const op = st.txn.operations[st.stepIndex];\n    st.stepIndex++;\n\n    // Check if failure is triggered mid-step\n    if (st.simulateFailure) {\n      logExec(\"!!! Simulated failure occurred DURING operation execution.\");\n      abortExecution(true);\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    if (op.op === \"read\") {\n      // For read operations, the value depends on isolation level\n      let val;\n      if (st.isolation === \"read_uncommitted\") {\n        // Read latest DB (own writes visible)\n        val = st.workingDB[op.key];\n      } else if (st.isolation === \"read_committed\") {\n        // Reads see DB snapshot (committed) - st.workingDB\n        val = st.workingDB[op.key];\n      } else if (st.isolation === \"repeatable_read\" || st.isolation === \"serializable\") {\n        // Cache repeated reads\n        if (op.key in st.readCache) {\n          val = st.readCache[op.key];\n        } else {\n          val = st.workingDB[op.key];\n          st.readCache[op.key] = val;\n        }\n      } else {\n        val = st.workingDB[op.key];\n      }\n      logExec(`READ '${op.key}' => '${val === undefined ? \"NULL\" : val}'`);\n    } else if (op.op === \"write\") {\n      // Before writing, check serializable conflicts:\n      if (st.isolation === \"serializable\") {\n        // Fail if key was already written once (simulate strong conflict detection)\n        if (st.serializableWrites.has(op.key)) {\n          logExec(`*** SERIALIZABLE Violation: Key '${op.key}' written multiple times. Aborting transaction.`);\n          abortExecution();\n          return false;\n        }\n        // Also fail if key is read previously and now written (read-write conflict)\n        if (st.readCache.hasOwnProperty(op.key)) {\n          logExec(`*** SERIALIZABLE Violation: Key '${op.key}' was read before and now written. Aborting transaction.`);\n          abortExecution();\n          return false;\n        }\n        st.serializableWrites.add(op.key);\n      }\n\n      // Writes buffer in committedWrites, updates workingDB view to simulate write visibility\n      st.committedWrites[op.key] = op.value;\n      st.workingDB[op.key] = op.value;\n      logExec(`WRITE '${op.key}' = '${op.value}' (buffered)`);\n    } else {\n      logExec(\"Unknown operation: \" + JSON.stringify(op));\n    }\n    refreshUI();\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Commit execution (atomic commit):\n  // All buffered writes applied or discarded depending on success\n  function commitExecution() {\n    if (!execState) return false;\n    if (execState.aborted) {\n      logExec(\"Cannot commit aborted transaction.\");\n      execState.finished = true;\n      execState = null;\n      refreshUI();\n      return false;\n    }\n    logExec(`Committing transaction '${execState.txn.id}'...`);\n\n    // Apply buffered writes atomically to the global database\n    if (!execState.durability) {\n      // Durability disabled: changes affect only current memory db without log\n      Object.entries(execState.committedWrites).forEach(([k,v]) => {\n        db[k] = v;\n      });\n    } else {\n      // Durability enabled: first write to durability log then apply\n      durabilityLog.push({\n        id: execState.txn.id,\n        operations: [...execState.txn.operations],\n        timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n        isolation: execState.isolation,\n        committedState: cloneDB(db),\n      });\n      // Apply writes\n      Object.entries(execState.committedWrites).forEach(([k,v]) => {\n        db[k] = v;\n      });\n      // Update durability log committedState with post-commit snapshot\n      durabilityLog[durabilityLog.length-1].committedState = cloneDB(db);\n    }\n\n    logExec(`Transaction '${execState.txn.id}' committed successfully.`);\n    logExec(\"Updated DB State:\\n\" + formatKV(db));\n    updateDBStateBox();\n\n    execState.finished = true;\n    execState = null;\n    refreshUI();\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  // Abort execution (rollback)\n  // hardAbort=true simulates failure, silent rollback\n  function abortExecution(hardAbort=false) {\n    if (!execState) return;\n    const id = execState.txn.id;\n    if (hardAbort) {\n      logExec(`Transaction '${id}' aborted due to failure (atomic rollback).`);\n    } else {\n      logExec(`Transaction '${id}' aborted by user. Rollback all writes.`);\n    }\n    // Rollback: do NOT apply any writes to global db, ignore buffered writes\n    execState.aborted = true;\n    execState.finished = true;\n    execState = null;\n    refreshUI();\n  }\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Auto-step helpers\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  function scheduleAutoStep() {\n    if (autoStepTimer) clearTimeout(autoStepTimer);\n    autoStepTimer = setTimeout(() => {\n      if (execState) {\n        let continueExec = stepExecution();\n        if (continueExec) {\n          scheduleAutoStep();\n        }\n      }\n    }, 1500);\n  }\n\n  function cancelAutoStep() {\n    if (autoStepTimer) {\n      clearTimeout(autoStepTimer);\n      autoStepTimer = null;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Button event bindings for execution and simulation\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  startExecBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (!currentTransaction) return;\n    if (execState) {\n      logExec(\"Execution already in progress.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    clearExecLog();\n    startExecution(\n      currentTransaction,\n      isolationSelect.value,\n      durabilityCheckbox.checked\n    );\n    if (!autoStep) {\n      logExec(\"Execution started. Use 'Step Operation' button below to proceed operation-by-operation.\");\n    }\n  });\n\n  // New button for step operation:\n  const stepOpBtn = document.createElement(\"button\");\n  stepOpBtn.type = \"button\";\n  stepOpBtn.id = \"step-op-btn\";\n  stepOpBtn.textContent = \"Step Operation\";\n  stepOpBtn.disabled = true;\n  document.getElementById(\"execution-section\").appendChild(stepOpBtn);\n\n  stepOpBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (!execState) {\n      logExec(\"No ongoing execution.\");\n      stepOpBtn.disabled = true;\n      refreshUI();\n      return;\n    }\n    const cont = stepExecution();\n    if (!cont) {\n      stepOpBtn.disabled = true;\n    }\n  });\n\n  // Enable stepOpBtn only if execState active and auto-step off\n  function refreshStepOpBtn() {\n    stepOpBtn.disabled = (execState === null) || autoStep;\n  }\n\n  // Simulate failure during execution\n  simulateFailureBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (execState) {\n      execState.simulateFailure = true;\n      logExec(\"Simulated failure requested. Next operation will cause abort.\");\n    }\n  });\n\n  // On execution state change, update stepOpBtn state\n  function onExecStateChange() {\n    refreshStepOpBtn();\n  }\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Exploration buttons\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  simulateCrashBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (execState) {\n      logExec(\"!!! Simulating system crash: current execution stopped and state lost.\");\n      execState = null;\n      refreshUI();\n      refreshStepOpBtn();\n    } else {\n      logExec(\"No execution in progress to crash.\");\n    }\n  });\n\n  recoverDbBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (durabilityLog.length === 0) {\n      logExec(\"No durability log present to recover from.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    // Recover DB by applying all committed transactions in durability log order\n    logExec(\"Recovering DB from durability log...\");\n    db = cloneDB(DEFAULT_DB); // start from default base\n    durabilityLog.forEach(entry => {\n      entry.operations.forEach(op => {\n        if (op.op === \"write\") {\n          db[op.key] = op.value;\n        }\n      });\n    });\n    logExec(\"Recovery complete. Current DB state:\\n\" + formatKV(db));\n    updateDBStateBox();\n  });\n\n  viewDurabilityLogBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    durabilityLogSection.style.display = \"block\";\n    renderDurabilityLog();\n  });\n\n  closeDurabilityLogBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    durabilityLogSection.style.display = \"none\";\n  });\n\n  clearLogBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    clearExecLog();\n  });\n\n  autoStepCheckbox.addEventListener(\"change\", () => {\n    autoStep = autoStepCheckbox.checked;\n    if (autoStep && execState) {\n      scheduleAutoStep();\n    } else {\n      cancelAutoStep();\n    }\n    refreshStepOpBtn();\n    refreshUI();\n  });\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Render durability log details\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  function renderDurabilityLog() {\n    if (durabilityLog.length === 0) {\n      durabilityLogBox.textContent = \"(Durability log is empty)\";\n      return;\n    }\n    let lines = durabilityLog.map((entry, idx) => {\n      let opsDesc = entry.operations.map(op => {\n        if (op.op === \"read\") return `READ ${op.key}`;\n        if (op.op === \"write\") return `WRITE ${op.key}='${op.value}'`;\n        return \"\";\n      }).join(\", \");\n      return `${idx+1}. [${entry.timestamp}] ID=${entry.id}, ISOLATION=${entry.isolation}\\n    Ops: ${opsDesc}`;\n    });\n    durabilityLogBox.textContent = lines.join(\"\\n\\n\");\n  }\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Initialize UI and State\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  function initialize() {\n    db = {...DEFAULT_DB};\n    updateDBStateBox();\n    updateCurrentTransactionInfo();\n    updateTransOpsBox();\n    refreshUI();\n    refreshStepOpBtn();\n  }\n\n  initialize();\n\n  // =======================================================================\n  // Accessibility & Keyboard shortcuts (optional)\n  // =======================================================================\n\n  // Enter on Transaction ID input triggers create transaction\n  transIdInput.addEventListener(\"keydown\", e => {\n    if (e.key === \"Enter\") {\n      e.preventDefault();\n      createTransBtn.click();\n    }\n  });\n\n  // Enter on opKeyInput and opValueInput tries to add operation if possible\n  opKeyInput.addEventListener(\"keydown\", e => {\n    if (e.key === \"Enter\" && !addOpBtn.disabled) {\n      e.preventDefault();\n      addOpBtn.click();\n    }\n  });\n\n  opValueInput.addEventListener(\"keydown\", e => {\n    if (e.key === \"Enter\" && !addOpBtn.disabled) {\n      e.preventDefault();\n      addOpBtn.click();\n    }\n  });\n\n  // After each stepExecution call, update stepOpBtn\n  const originalStepExecution = stepExecution;\n  stepExecution = function() {\n    const cont = originalStepExecution();\n    onExecStateChange();\n    return cont;\n  };\n\n  // After startExecution we update stepOpBtn state as well\n  const originalStartExecution = startExecution;\n  startExecution = function(txn, isolation, durability) {\n    originalStartExecution(txn, isolation, durability);\n    onExecStateChange();\n  };\n\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
